                    <item_0
                        jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                        sling:resourceType="core/franklin/components/block/v1/block/item"
                        model="text-container-text"
                        modelFields="[text]"
                        name="Text Container Text"
                        text="&lt;p>Centro de Salud Familiar clinic serves about 13,000 people annually. It is the only provider of primary and preventive health service for Arroyo, Guayama and the surrounding rural areas.&lt;/p>&lt;p>The clinic received an emergency grant from Direct Relief to help bring it back to full strength after Maria caused wind and water damage. The clinic is also a recipient of the AbbVie donation, which funded a custom-built mobile medical unit to reach community members in rural, mountainous areas.&lt;/p>&lt;p>Yesenia Ortiz, 27, works at the clinic as a health records clerk. Her family home in Arroyo was so badly damaged that it had to be demolished and rebuilt, a slow process that is not quite complete over a year later.&lt;/p>"/>
                </block_17>
